# Use Next.js Image for images

- **Always use** `import Image from 'next/image'` and `<Image />` instead of `<img>`.
- Provide `width` and `height` (or use `fill` with a sized parent) so layout is stable.
- Use `alt` for accessibility; use `alt=""` only when the image is decorative.
- Add new image origins to `next.config` under `images.remotePatterns` or `images.localPatterns` when needed.

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid
<img src={url} alt="Thumbnail" className="rounded-lg" />

// ✅ Prefer
<Image src={url} alt="Thumbnail" width={56} height={56} className="rounded-lg object-cover" />
```
